'''Dae-Sook Suh''' (born 1931 )<ref>Library of Congress Authority File</ref>  is a professor [[emeritus]] of [[political science]] and the former director of the Centre for Korean Studies at the [[University of Hawaii]].<ref>https://cup.columbia.edu/book/kim-il-sung/9780231065733</ref> He received his PhD. from Columbia University  in 1964 with a thesis "[[Communism in Korea|Korean Communism]] and the rise of [[Kim Il Sung|Kim]]" <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/korean-communism-and-the-rise-of-kim/oclc/36608890&referer=brief_results] WorldCat Thesis information page</ref>

He is best known for  the books [[Kim Il Sung: The North Korean Leader]] which was published by [[Columbia University Press]] and 'The Korean Communist Movement'.<ref>http://www.washington.edu/uwpress/search/books/SUHPOL.html</ref> His works have been published or translated in English, Korean, Russian, and Germman.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}

